## Workflow

```
/setup              → configure kitt for this project (run once)
/setup validate     → check configuration completeness
/workflow-orchestrator → start working on a ticket
```

## Skills (via Kitt)

| Skill | When to Use |
|-------|-------------|
| `workflow-orchestrator` | Route to the right workflow step |
| `refinement` | Before design — discover constraints |
| `architecture-alignment` | After refinement — validate architecture |
| `plan-building` | After alignment — create implementation plan |
| `implementor` | Execute the plan with TDD |
| `branch-creator` | Create branch from ticket |
| `pr-creator` | Create PR with task manager integration |

## Context Files

Skills read these before acting — keep them accurate:

- `.claude/context/product.md` — domain, users, business rules
- `.claude/context/tech-stack.md` — stack, infra, databases
- `.claude/context/code-standards.md` — architecture, naming, testing

## Hard Rules

- **NEVER push without explicit confirmation**
- **NEVER commit without user review first**
- When uncertain about a pattern: search first, ask if unclear, never guess

